contract hardening day

Today was mostly about tightening the release-facing boundaries around Codexify rather than chasing new product surface area. The work fell into two lanes: beta delivery hardening for the public webUI path, and contract/planning work for Pi-based coding agent integration. Both mattered because they reduced ambiguity about what the system is supposed to do, what is actually wired, and what still needs proof before anyone treats it as release truth.

